#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:3
msgid "How to Extend the Framework"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:5
msgid ""
"The framework is rapidly evolving. The documentation might be out-of-sync "
"with the implementation. The purpose of this documentation is to give "
"context for upcoming reviews."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:9
msgid ""
"SSAF is designed to be extensible with new **summary extractors** and "
"**serialization formats**. Extensions can be added in three ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:12
msgid ""
"**Statically, in-tree** — built as part of the upstream LLVM/Clang tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:13
msgid ""
"**Statically, out-of-tree (downstream)** — built in a downstream fork or "
"project that links ``clangScalableStaticAnalysisFrameworkCore`` as a static "
"library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:14
msgid "**Dynamically, via plugins** — loaded at runtime as shared objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:16
msgid ""
"All three approaches use the same ``llvm::Registry``-based registration "
"mechanism. The key difference is how the linker sees the registration: "
"static libraries need :doc:`force-linker anchors <ForceLinkerHeaders>` to "
"prevent dead-stripping, while shared libraries do not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:21
msgid "Adding a summary extractor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:23
msgid ""
"A summary extractor is an ``ASTConsumer`` that inspects the AST and "
"populates a ``TUSummary`` via the ``TUSummaryBuilder`` interface."
msgstr ""

