#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:207
msgid "Dynamic extensibility (plugins)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:209
msgid ""
"Shared libraries loaded at runtime — via ``dlopen`` / ``LoadLibrary`` or the "
"Clang plugin mechanism — do **not** need force-linker anchors, but having "
"them also does not hurt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:212
msgid ""
"When a shared object (``.so`` / ``.dylib``) is loaded, the dynamic linker "
"runs all global constructors in that library unconditionally. This means the "
"``llvm::Registry::Add<>`` objects execute their constructors and register "
"themselves automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:215
msgid "To use a plugin:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:217
msgid "Build your extractor or format as a shared library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:218
msgid "Load it with the Clang plugin mechanism (``-fplugin=`` or ``-load``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:219
msgid "Pass the extractor name to ``--ssaf-extract-summaries=`` as usual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ScalableStaticAnalysisFramework/developer-docs/HowToExtend.rst:221
msgid ""
"No changes to any force-linker header are required. The ``llvm::Registry`` "
"infrastructure handles everything once the shared object is loaded."
msgstr ""
